article.headline: Wichita State 77, UMKC 55
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- P.J. Couisnard and Sean Ogirri combined for 29 points to lead Wichita State to a 77-55 win over Missouri-Kansas City on Saturday night. Wichita State (8-2) led only 35-29 at halftime, but Couisnard scored the first nine points of the second half to give the Shockers a cushion. Couisnard had two steals for lay-ups, two free throws and a 3-point basket from the right corner as the Shockers took a 44-29 lead just two minutes into the second half. UMKC (3-5) got within 52-40 when Brent Stephens hit a 3-point shot with 11:39 left. Then Ogirri, who finished with 15 points, started hitting from long range. He made three 3-point shots within two minutes to give Wichita State a 61-42 lead with 9:04 left. He finished 5-of-7 from 3-point range. The largest lead for the Shockers was 75-49 with 2:36 left. The loss extended the Kangaroos' losing streak to four games. Quinton Day led UMKC with a game-high 16 points, and Tim Blackwell had 12.
